usfktcjelotgggtcmcmoikyaqoycusxoqqiqfauc length 5 62826 page 1875 Wiki project devoted to linguistics This article needs additional citations for verification. Please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed. Find sources: "Glottopedia" – news · newspapers · books · scholar · JSTOR (September 2017) (template removal help) Glottopedia Type of site Wiki for linguistics Available in English, German, etc. URL www.glottopedia.org Registration Optional (required to edit pages) Users 356 [1] Launched 27 May 2007 Current status Active Content license Creative Commons CC-BY-SA[2] Glottopedia is a wiki devoted to linguistics. Glottopedia was created on 27 May 2007 as a merger of two earlier projects, WikiLingua at the University of Trier (created in 2005), and Linguipedia at the Max Planck Institute for Evolutionary Anthropology in Leipzig (created in 2006).[2] Many or most of its topics are as of May 2016[update] treated on two pages, in English and German respectively. The content is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 licence.[2] It is implemented with the MediaWiki wiki engine, and limits editing to registered contributors with their real names.[2] As of 2021, it has about 3,200 content pages by 356 registered users.[3] Notes[edit] ^ "Statistics-Glottopedia". Retrieved 14 April 2021. ^ a b c d "Glottopedia:About". Glottopedia. Retrieved 2017-03-29. ^ "Statistics - Glottopedia". Retrieved 14 April 2021. External links[edit] Glottopedia Kerstin Haunstetter (2010). "Glottopedia – die kostenlose Online-Enzyklopädie im Vergleich mit den Wörterbüchern zur Sprach- und Kommunikationswissenschaft". Lexicographica. Tome 26, Pages 229–248. 26 (2010): 229–248. doi:10.1515/9783110223231.3.229. S2CID 184850872. This article about a linguistics organization is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. v t e contentType 24 text/html; charset=UTF-8 url 45 https://en.wikipedia.org:4